

    One way to copy the local host files to guest OS ( Hyper-VM ) 

    1.Turn it off Virtual Machine.
    2.Locate virtual hard disk image file .vhd of the particular VM.
    3.Right click on this file and select mount
    4.Would now find  "System Reserved" and "Local Disk" drives.
    5.Open the "Local Disk" drive (this is the OS drive on VM)
    6.Paste you files.
    7.Eject from the drivers
    8.Run the Virtusl Machine and one can locate find the just copied files in the corresponding C:\ folders.
